For Ubuntu Touch:
Open ubuntu-sdk and use the Ubuntu kit > 15.04

open libosmscout/libosmscout.pro
run qmake
build project
copy the resulting libosmscout.a to OSMScout2/libs/libosmscout.a

open libosmscout-map/libosmscout-map.pro
run qmake
build project
copy the resulting libosmscout-map.a to OSMScout2/libs/libosmscout-map.a

open libosmscout-map-qt/libosmscout-map-qt.pro
run qmake
build project
copy the resulting libosmscout-map-qt.a to OSMScout2/libs/libosmscout-map-qt.a

Now open OSMScout2/OSMScout.pro
run qmake
build the project
Create Click package and install on device.

When running, the application requires a map to start. 
For now, the map files should go into /media/phablet/<SD_CARD>/Pictures/osmscout
The files should be imported on a PC using the Import tool, please refer to the libosmscout documentation for instructions



You can find detailed instruction how to get libraries and applications
build and working in the openstreetmap wiki:

http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Libosmscout
